-- Turkish Jobless Falls to 10.4% in February
-- B y   A l i   B e r a t   M e r i c
-- 2012-05-15T07:09:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-15/turkish-jobless-falls-to-10-4-in-february-correct-.html
(Corrects month in headline.)  Turkish  unemployment  fell to 10.4
percent in February from 11.5 percent in the same month of last
year.  The rate rose from 10.2 percent in January, the statistics
office in Ankara said on its website today.  On an adjusted basis, the jobless rate was 9.1 percent
compared with 9 percent in January, and declining from 10.1
percent in the same month of last year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ali Berat Meric in Ankara at 
 americ@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
